        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T18:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <head>Inhabitants of Plaistow</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Plaistow</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:00" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">From the inhabitants of Plaistow, Essex, England, in
                            public meeting assembled</hi>.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">To Mrs. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lincoln:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Madam</hi>: Many words in your present grief would
                        be an intrusion. “We have expressed in another form our sympathy with the
                        loss sustained by the United States as a nation. Here, and to you, we would
                        only say that, as men and women of kindred race to your own, and, therefore,
                        of the same Christian family, we fully share in the grief felt by those more
                        immediately near to you. Distance does not create division in a common
                        sorrow; may that sorrow felt most keenly by yourself be assuaged by the
                        Great Healer, and to his tender mercy we affectionately commit you and
                        yours.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Signed on behalf of the meeting:</salute>
                    <signed>JOHN FOSTER, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chairman</hi>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
